    "discriminators": [
     "Nothing else in AIRCRAFT sounds like this. There is no engine and no rotor: the burner is a turbulent, unpitched propane roar of a few seconds, then near-silence as the balloon drifts. That silence between burns is as diagnostic as the burn.",
     "Acoustically the burner IS a FIRE-TURBULENT blast — same physics, same statistics. DSP will narrow to 'turbulent gas roar' and stop there; only the words balloon, burner, propane, airship or blimp commit it to AIRCRAFT. Never assert this from signal alone.",
     "Separate it from AIRCRAFT-JET and MOTORS-TURBINE by the absence of any sustained tonal core — a jet has a screaming harmonic whine riding on its noise, a burner has none. The envelope flapping in the wind is CLOTH-FLAP; the inflation fan is MACHINES-FAN."
    ],
