    "discriminators": [
     "An LP-filtered rumble bed. The fuselage is a low-pass filter: band_limit_high_hz falls to a few kHz, low_band_energy dominates at ~0.62, spectral_slope_db_per_octave is steeply negative, and stationarity is very high because a cruising cabin is essentially room tone. LP + stationary is a real measurement and it prunes hard.",
     "Against AIRCRAFT-JET (exterior): the exterior jet keeps its full broadband HF roar and is far brighter (spectral_centroid_hz ~1.4 kHz vs ~350 Hz here). This boundary is genuinely measurable.",
     "Against BOATS-INTERIOR / TRAINS-INTERIOR: identical morphology — which vehicle you are inside is semantic. The one honest physical tell is that a TRAIN interior carries the wheel clack through the floor (onset_periodicity rises to ~0.45), while an aircraft cabin has no periodic component at all."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
