    "discriminators": [
     "A turbine is a BROADBAND ROAR: jet efflux is turbulent mixing noise, which is stochastic by nature. High spectral_flatness (~0.62, gated >= 0.20), low harmonicity, wide complexity — and, decisively, NO blade-pass periodicity. onset_periodicity is gated at a maximum of 0.55 and expected near 0.13.",
     "That periodicity axis is what genuinely separates JET from PROP and HELICOPTER, and it deserves stating plainly: prop and rotor aircraft stamp a MECHANICAL REPETITION RATE onto the noise (a blade sweeping past, over and over); a jet does not, because nothing about it repeats. Every other property of these three — loud, long, LF-weighted, noisy — is shared.",
     "Against AIRCRAFT-MILITARY and AIRCRAFT-ROCKET: the same broadband-roar morphology, so DSP cannot finish. A rocket is louder, lower and flatter still; a military jet is acoustically just a jet. Text decides.",
     "A pass-by adds doppler — spectral_centroid_slope_hz_per_second crossing through zero with a rise-fall envelope — but that identifies a PERSPECTIVE, not a different aircraft."
