    "discriminators": [
     "Blade-pass again, but FUSED. A propeller at ~2400 rpm with 2-3 blades puts the blade-pass fundamental at 80-120 Hz — above the ~20 Hz ceiling at which the ear resolves separate events — so it is heard as a PITCHED BUZZ with a HARMONIC COMB rather than a train of thumps. Hence sustained_tonal, a measurable pitch_hz near 95 Hz, a high partial_count (the comb), and harmonicity well off the noise floor.",
     "Against AIRCRAFT-JET: the jet has no blade-pass structure at all. spectral_flatness ~0.62 and harmonicity ~0.15 there against ~0.35 and ~0.48 here. The harmonicity/periodicity axis is the genuine, physical separator between jet and prop — not a semantic one.",
     "Against AIRCRAFT-HELICOPTER: identical mechanism, an order of magnitude apart in rate. The rotor's 10-20 Hz blade-pass resolves into discrete onsets (onset_rate_per_second ~12, onset_periodicity ~0.78 and a hard LF gate); the propeller's does not.",
     "Against AIRCRAFT-RADIO CONTROLLED: pitch_hz is the whole story — ~95 Hz here against several hundred Hz for a small, fast RC rotor, with the spectral tilt inverted."
